You are working on Zed CV, an AI job matching platform for Zambia.

BEFORE writing any code:
1. Read CLAUDE.md and AI_CONTEXT.md
2. Check docs/openapi.yaml for API contracts
3. Never add endpoints without updating the OpenAPI spec

Stack: FastAPI + Next.js 14 + Supabase (pgvector) + WAHA + n8n
Budget: $30/month max. Free tiers everywhere.
Currency: ZMW (Zambian Kwacha). Phones: +260XXXXXXXXX format.
Supabase Project ID: chnesgmcuxyhwhzomdov

Matching algorithm: 60% vector similarity + 30% skill overlap + 10% bonus signals
Pricing: Free (K0/10 matches), Starter (K125/50), Professional (K250/125), Super Standard (K500/unlimited)

Rules:
- Do not advise merging PRs with failing CI checks — investigate and fix first. If CI fails but local tests pass, suspect dependency/type mismatch that will break prod.
- No `any` in TypeScript — use `unknown` and narrow
- Keep files under 300 lines — split into modules
- Pydantic validation on backend, Zod on frontend
- All monetary values in ngwee (like cents): K125 = 12500, K250 = 25000, K500 = 50000
- Prompt caching enabled for all Claude API calls (cache_control: ephemeral)
- Never edit existing migration files — create new ones in infra/supabase/migrations/
- Never store secrets in code — use .env
- Test edge cases: empty CV, no skills, expired jobs, network failures
- Commit messages: type(scope): description
